title: Detective Comics 27-33 + Batman 01-07 (1939-1941|Dgtl|G85+M-E)
description: On March 30, 1939, Batman debuted in the pages of Detective Comics. Today, as I post this, it has been exactly 75 years since then - of amazing stories, timeless villains, fantastic films and thrilling television, and even recently some great games and much more - all about the Dark Knight and his family of costumed fighters. Celebrate this pop culture icon with the ones that started it all - his first appearances as well as the first seven issues of his title run. These are all-digital editions of the landmark issues - the Detective Comics stuff is Batman stories only, thanks to Monfekk-Empire, and the Batman stuff is G85-Empire's works. Thanks SO MUCH to the scanner groups for these awesome copies, please enjoy and seed - and long live the Caped Crusader and the Dynamic Duo forevermore! :-)
